The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Friday, October 24, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Friday, October 24, 2003				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Central Avenue, at Esplanade, for work on the flyover. North-bound traffic to take Rani Rashmoni Road. South-bound traffic will be diverted down Madan Street and S.N. Banerjee Road. 				 																United Nations Day				 																																	A debate on United Nations Needs to be Reformed, to mark the occasion, at Mahajati Sadan, 10.30 am. Speaker of the Assembly Hashim Abdul Halim will attend.				 																Music medley				 																																	A performance of Baul and Calypso, Bangla band in Punjabi style, in English, Hindi, Bengali and Punjabi, by singer Sumit Roy at Nik-Nish, Metro Shopping Centre, from 4 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition of paintings by Nitya Kundu and Ranajit Hira at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm to 8 pm.
